claim.claim-text:
9. A method for monitoring a microsample in a flow measuring cell of an analyzer comprising:
providing an analyzer including a flow measuring cell and a device comprising at least one electrode system, each said system comprising at least two single electrodes;
introducing a microsample into said flow measuring cell, said microsample passing said electrode system;
measuring at least one substance contained in the microsample by applying a measurement voltage to said flow measuring cell, which said measurement voltage is essentially a DC voltage; and
detecting the absence of bubbles and/or position of said microsample in an area of said at least one electrode system by applying an alternating voltage to said flow measuring cell simultaneous with said measurement voltage via two single electrodes of said at least one electrode system, and detecting the AC component or impedance.
